    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the `gc` mapping is used to comment code with TreeSitter commentstring, the `FileType` event is triggered in a ~~non-existent~~ buffer with a filename matching the filetype (ie. `lua` for lua files)\n\nThis only happens the first time code is commented - after that, the event seems to no longer be triggered\n\n~~This breaks `FileType` autocmds because it means the `abuf` bufnr can be invalid~~\n\nThe buffer seems to exist when the autocmd is triggered, but is then destroyed. Here is my autocmd, which is broken by this:\n\n```lua\nlocal ts = require(\"nvim-treesitter\")\nlocal langs = ts.get_available()\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\n  callback = function(args)\n    local filetype = args.match\n    local lang = vim.treesitter.language.get_lang(filetype)\n\n    if not vim.tbl_contains(langs, lang) then\n      return\n    end\n\n    ts.install({ lang }):await(function()\n\t  -- This will fail because the buffer will be deleted\n      vim.treesitter.start(args.buf, lang)\n    end)\n  end,\n})\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `touch foo.lua`\n2. `nvim --clean foo.lua`\n3. `:lua vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {callback = function(a) print(vim.inspect(a)) end})`\n4. Type any code\n5. Press `gcc` on the line\n\n<img width=\"408\" height=\"340\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/210251e0-7830-47a0-89ab-d8f959070979\" />\n\n<img width=\"398\" height=\"120\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d204cf58-3c24-4061-b9a6-aaffada1fb5e\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe event shouldn't be triggered\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+1569-16c815222\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.3-1.202511061625.fc43\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nnvim-nightly copr",
