            "body": "Here I only collected what I described somewhere else about a year ago, having a similar problem (didn't find that issue/discussion). \n\nCurrently we (and unfortunately plugin authors, including built-in ones) have to work around this (e.g. by checking `buftype`) to avoid the possibly costly effects of `FileType` autocommands (for me it was starting LSP servers - `vim.lsp.enable()` introduced later have such guard so I could remove equivalents on the my side).",
